# Performance Patterns

## Overview

Performance optimizations focus on reducing unnecessary API calls and improving user experience through lazy loading, smart caching, and efficient data management.

## Problem Statement

The original approach fetched all data immediately when opening a task:

```javascript
// ❌ Old approach - fetch everything immediately
useEffect(() => {
  if (isOpen && task) {
    fetchUsers();
    fetchExistingTags();
    loadHistory(task.id);      // Always fetched
    loadActivity(task.id);     // Always fetched
  }
}, [task, isOpen]);
```

**Issues**:

- Users who only view task details still pay for History/Activity API calls
- Slower modal open time (waiting for 4 API calls)
- Wasted bandwidth and server resources
- Poor user experience on slow connections

## Lazy Loading

Load data only when needed, not upfront.

### Tab-Based Lazy Loading

For modals or pages with tabs:

```jsx
const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState(0);
const [historyLoaded, setHistoryLoaded] = useState(false);
const [activityLoaded, setActivityLoaded] = useState(false);

// Don't load on mount
useEffect(() => {
  if (isOpen) {
    setActiveTab(0);
    setHistoryLoaded(false);
    setActivityLoaded(false);
  }
}, [isOpen]);

// Load on tab click
const handleTabChange = (index) => {
  setActiveTab(index);
  
  if (index === 1 && !historyLoaded) {
    loadHistory();
  } else if (index === 2 && !activityLoaded) {
    loadActivity();
  }
};

// Load function with caching
const loadHistory = async () => {
  if (historyLoaded) return; // Skip if loaded
  
  setLoadingHistory(true);
  try {
    const data = await fetchHistory();
    setHistory(data);
    setHistoryLoaded(true);
  } finally {
    setLoadingHistory(false);
  }
};
```

### Benefits

1. **Faster Initial Load**
   - Only 2 API calls instead of 4
   - Modal opens ~500-1000ms faster
   - Better perceived performance

2. **Reduced Server Load**
   - 50% fewer API calls for users who don't view tabs
   - Less database queries
   - Lower bandwidth usage

3. **Smart Caching**
   - Data cached after first load
   - No redundant requests on tab switches
   - Cache invalidated after updates

4. **Better UX**
   - Instant modal open
   - Data loads quickly when needed
   - Loading indicators show progress

## Cache Invalidation

Reset loaded flags after mutations to ensure fresh data:

```jsx
const handleUpdate = async () => {
  await updateTask(taskId, data);
  
  // Invalidate caches
  setHistoryLoaded(false);
  setActivityLoaded(false);
  
  // Only reload if user is viewing that tab
  if (activeTab === 1) {
    await loadHistory();
  } else if (activeTab === 2) {
    await loadActivity();
  }
};
```

### Modal Reset

Reset state when opening a new task:

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  if (isOpen) {
    // Reset tab to Comments
    setActiveTab(0);
    
    // Reset loaded flags for new task
    setHistoryLoaded(false);
    setActivityLoaded(false);
    
    // Don't fetch History/Activity - wait for tab click
  }
}, [task, isOpen]);
```

## Loading States

Always show progress during async operations.

### Button Loading

```jsx
<button
  type="submit"
  disabled={isSubmitting}
  className="btn-primary disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed flex items-center gap-2"
>
  {isSubmitting && (
    <svg className="animate-spin h-4 w-4 text-white" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
      <circle className="opacity-25" cx="12" cy="12" r="10" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth="4"></circle>
      <path className="opacity-75" fill="currentColor" d="M4 12a8 8 0 018-8V0C5.373 0 0 5.373 0 12h4zm2 5.291A7.962 7.962 0 014 12H0c0 3.042 1.135 5.824 3 7.938l3-2.647z"></path>
    </svg>
  )}
  {isSubmitting ? "Updating..." : "Update Task"}
</button>
```

### Form Overlay

```jsx
<form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className="relative">
  {/* Loading Overlay */}
  {isSubmitting && (
    <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-dark-900/50 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-lg z-10 flex items-center justify-center">
      <div className="flex flex-col items-center gap-3">
        <div className="inline-block w-12 h-12 border-4 border-primary-600 border-t-transparent rounded-full animate-spin"></div>
        <p className="text-dark-200 font-medium">Updating task...</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  )}
  
  {/* Form content */}
</form>
```

