## Double-Submission Prevention

Always prevent duplicate submissions:

```jsx
const [isSubmitting, setIsSubmitting] = useState(false);

const handleSubmit = async (e) => {
  e.preventDefault();
  
  // Early return if already submitting
  if (isSubmitting) return;
  
  setIsSubmitting(true);
  
  try {
    await saveData();
    showToast("Saved successfully", "success");
  } catch (error) {
    showToast(error.message, "error");
  } finally {
    setIsSubmitting(false); // Always reset
  }
};
```

## API Call Reduction

### Before Optimization

```jsx
// ❌ Bad - loads everything upfront
useEffect(() => {
  if (isOpen && task) {
    fetchUsers();
    fetchTags();
    fetchHistory();    // Not always needed
    fetchActivity();   // Not always needed
  }
}, [isOpen, task]);

// Result: 4 API calls every time
```

### After Optimization

```jsx
// ✅ Good - loads on demand
useEffect(() => {
  if (isOpen && task) {
    fetchUsers();      // Needed for dropdown
    fetchTags();       // Needed for autocomplete
    // History/Activity loaded on tab click
  }
}, [isOpen, task]);

// Result: 2 API calls initially, 50% reduction
```

## Metrics to Track

Monitor these to measure performance:

1. **API Call Count**
   - Calls per modal open
   - Calls per update
   - Cache hit rate

2. **Load Times**
   - Time to modal open
   - Time to first interaction
   - Time to data load

3. **User Behavior**
   - % who view each tab
   - Average tabs per session
   - Most common workflows

4. **Error Rates**
   - Failed lazy loads
   - Timeout errors
   - Cache invalidation issues

## Best Practices

### 1. Load Only What's Visible

```jsx
// ✅ Good
if (tabVisible && !dataLoaded) {
  loadData();
}

// ❌ Bad
loadAllData(); // Even if not visible
```

### 2. Cache Loaded Data

```jsx
// ✅ Good
const [dataLoaded, setDataLoaded] = useState(false);

if (!dataLoaded) {
  const data = await fetchData();
  setDataLoaded(true);
}

// ❌ Bad
const data = await fetchData(); // Every time
```

### 3. Invalidate After Mutations

```jsx
// ✅ Good
await updateTask();
setHistoryLoaded(false); // Force reload

// ❌ Bad
await updateTask();
// History shows stale data
```

### 4. Show Loading States

```jsx
// ✅ Good
{loading ? <Spinner /> : <Content />}

// ❌ Bad
<Content /> // No feedback
```

### 5. Prevent Double Actions

```jsx
// ✅ Good
if (isSubmitting) return;
setIsSubmitting(true);

// ❌ Bad
setIsSubmitting(true); // Can be called twice
```

### 6. Handle Errors Gracefully

Don't let failed lazy loads break the UI:

```jsx
// ✅ Good - error handling
try {
  await loadHistory();
} catch (error) {
  console.error("Failed to load history:", error);
  showToast("Failed to load history", "error");
}

// ❌ Bad - unhandled errors
await loadHistory(); // Might crash
```

## Common Patterns

### Modal with Tabs

```jsx
const Modal = ({ isOpen, task }) => {
  const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState(0);
  const [loaded, setLoaded] = useState({
    history: false,
    activity: false
  });
  
  useEffect(() => {
    if (isOpen) {
      setActiveTab(0);
      setLoaded({ history: false, activity: false });
    }
  }, [isOpen]);
  
  const handleTabChange = (index) => {
    setActiveTab(index);
    
    if (index === 1 && !loaded.history) {
      loadHistory();
    } else if (index === 2 && !loaded.activity) {
      loadActivity();
    }
  };
  
  return (
    <Tab.Group selectedIndex={activeTab} onChange={handleTabChange}>
      {/* tabs */}
    </Tab.Group>
  );
};
```

### Form with Loading

```jsx
const Form = () => {
  const [isSubmitting, setIsSubmitting] = useState(false);
  
  const handleSubmit = async (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    if (isSubmitting) return;
    
    setIsSubmitting(true);
    try {
      await saveData();
      showToast("Success", "success");
    } catch (error) {
      showToast(error.message, "error");
    } finally {
      setIsSubmitting(false);
    }
  };
  
  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className="relative">
      {isSubmitting && <LoadingOverlay />}
      
      <button disabled={isSubmitting}>
        {isSubmitting ? "Saving..." : "Save"}
      </button>
    </form>
  );
};
```

## Future Optimizations

Consider these improvements for better performance:

### 1. Prefetching

Prefetch data when user hovers over tabs:

```jsx
const handleTabHover = (index) => {
  if (index === 1 && !historyLoaded && !loadingHistory) {
    // Start loading in background
    loadHistory(internalTask.id);
  }
};

<Tab onMouseEnter={() => handleTabHover(1)}>
  History
</Tab>
```

### 2. Pagination

Load data in chunks for large datasets:

```jsx
const loadHistory = async (taskId, page = 1, limit = 20) => {
  const response = await fetchTaskHistory(taskId, { page, limit });
  setHistory(prev => [...prev, ...response.data]);
};
```

### 3. Virtual Scrolling

Render only visible items for long lists:

```jsx
import { FixedSizeList } from "react-window";

<FixedSizeList
  height={400}
  itemCount={history.length}
  itemSize={80}
>
  {({ index, style }) => (
    <HistoryItem data={history[index]} style={style} />
  )}
</FixedSizeList>
```

### 4. Request Deduplication

Prevent duplicate requests for the same data:

```jsx
const requestCache = new Map();

const loadHistory = async (taskId) => {
  const cacheKey = `history-${taskId}`;
  
  // Return existing promise if request is in flight
  if (requestCache.has(cacheKey)) {
    return requestCache.get(cacheKey);
  }
  
  const promise = fetchTaskHistory(taskId);
  requestCache.set(cacheKey, promise);
  
  try {
    const data = await promise;
    return data;
  } finally {
    requestCache.delete(cacheKey);
  }
};
```

### 5. Optimistic Updates

Update UI immediately, revert on error:

```jsx
const updateTask = async (taskId, updates) => {
  // Update UI immediately
  setInternalTask(prev => ({ ...prev, ...updates }));
  
  try {
    // Send to server
    await api.patch(`/tasks/${taskId}`, updates);
  } catch (error) {
    // Revert on error
    setInternalTask(originalTask);
    showToast("Update failed", "error");
  }
};
```

